com.yantra.yfc.rcp

Class YRCDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.jface.window.Window
      • org.eclipse.jface.dialogs.Dialog
        • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.jface.window.IShellProvider

    public class YRCDialog
extends org.eclipse.jface.dialogs.Dialog
    A specialized dialog window used for focused communication with the user.

    YRCDialog are usually modal. Consequently, it is generally bad practice to open a dialog without a parent. A modal dialog without a parent is not prevented from disappearing behind the application's other windows, making it very confusing for the user.

    If there is more than one modal dialog is open the second one should be parented off of the shell of the first one otherwise it is possible that the OS will give focus to the first dialog potentially blocking the UI.

      • setShellStyle

        public void setShellStyle(int newShellStyle)
        This Method should be called to change shell style in non extension mode.
        By Default style used is :
        In Extension Mode - SWT.SHELL_TRIM
        Otherwise - SWT.APPLICATION_MODAL | SWT.RESIZE | SWT.CLOSE | SWT.BORDER

        Note - This method should be called before opening YRCDialog
